{(s_n)}
\sigma_n
\sigma_n = \frac{s_0 +s_1 + ... + s_n}{n+1}
M < \infty, |na_n| \leq M
{\sigma_n = \sigma}
s_n = \sigma
m <n
s_n - \sigma_n = \frac{m+1}{n-m}(\sigma_n -\sigma_m) + \frac{1}{n-m}\sum_{i=m+1}^n (s_n -s_i)
|s_n - s_i|\leq\frac{(n-1)M}{i+1}\leq\frac{(n-m-1)M}{m+2}
\epsilon>1
m\leq\frac{n-\epsilon}{1+\epsilon}<m+1
(m+1)/(n-m) \leq \frac{1}{\epsilon}
|s_n -s_i|<M\epsilon
\epsilon
s_n = \sigma
